    "adventorial_article_7fKJMB": {
      "type": "adventorial-article",
      "custom_css": [],
      "name": "Adventorial Article",
      "settings": {
        "button_bg": "#000000",
        "button_text_color": "#ffffff",
        "button_radius": 6,
        "button_font": "inherit",
        "button_font_size": 16,
        "button_font_size_mobile": 16,
        "title": "",
        "subtitle": "",
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/3-66_1.webp",
        "mobile_image": "shopify://shop_images/srmobile.webp",
        "content": "<p>I’m rough on gear. If it lives in my world—boots, tools, bikes, phones—it’s eventually getting scratched, dropped, or buried in sawdust.<br/><br/>I’ve had an Apple Watch for a while and I genuinely like it. The problem is I’m a full-time woodworker. My “office” is a shop where everything has a sharp edge, a hard corner, or dust floating in the air. Add in weekends spent riding, hiking, hunting, and trying to pretend I still surf, and that tiny glass screen started feeling like a bad idea.<br/><br/>Every time I walked into the shop with my Apple Watch on, I was half-worried I’d smack it into a clamp or a table saw fence and watch $800 explode on my wrist.<br/><br/>That’s what pushed me to try the <a href=\"/products/carbinox-blaze\" title=\"Carbinox Blaze – Heavy Duty Smartwatch\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Carbinox Blaze</strong></span></a>—not to replace my Apple Watch, but to give it a tougher friend that could take the beating for it. I’ve been wearing the <a href=\"/products/carbinox-blaze\" title=\"Carbinox Blaze – Heavy Duty Smartwatch\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Blaze</strong></span> </a>for six months straight in my workshop and on every “dirty” day since.<br/><br/>Here’s the honest rundown.</p>",
        "show_button": false,
        "button_label": "CLICK HERE TO CHECK AVAILABILITY",
        "button_url": "",
        "button_new_tab": false,
        "show_divider": true
      }
    },
    "advertorial_article_structured_NnF7YX": {
      "type": "advertorial-article-structured",
      "blocks": {
        "subtitle_6wkAUN": {
          "type": "subtitle",
          "settings": {
            "subtitle": "What I Like"
          }
        },
        "text_FAwiw3": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<ul><li>I stop thinking about the watch once I put it on — it just takes abuse </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Battery easily lasts through long work days and weekend trips on a single charge </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Still gives me the smart stuff I actually use (calls, texts, notifications, heart rate, steps, sleep) </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Switching between Apple Watch off-duty and <a href=\"/products/carbinox-blaze\" title=\"Carbinox Blaze – Heavy Duty Smartwatch\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Blaze</strong></span></a> on-duty feels natural, not like a downgrade </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>The lifetime replacement warranty and 45-day trial made it an easy “why not” decision</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "subtitle_eWUdm8": {
          "type": "subtitle",
          "settings": {
            "subtitle": "What I Don’t Like"
          }
        },
        "text_KqW3DE": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<ul><li>The screen and body are a bit chunkier than my Apple Watch (makes sense for a work watch, but worth noting) </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Menus aren’t as “buttery” or polished as Apple’s — they’re more functional than fancy </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>You’ll probably end up liking it so much you feel guilty about how little you wear your Apple Watch to work</li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
